<br>
However other skills apply that make for better soloing in situations like PoP.<br>
<br>
(1) The ability to SLOW a mob (shaman, enchanter)<br>
(2) The ability to do damage without getting hit <br>
---(a)  Quad-kite/swarm-kite (Wizard, Druid, Bard)<br>
---(b)  Snare/Fear (necro, SK, ranger vs. animals)<br>
<br>
*I'm not sure how well snare/fear works in PoP really, but it has always been a strategy before*<br>
<br>
Being able to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>mitigate</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> mob damage is the big issue, because PoP mobs hit HARD.  Even tiny little birds hit for 250's. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
