Also want to add- I dont have my epic, no FT items and no uber gear at all. Also I never chain pets and only cannipet very rarely. The key is finding the right places to hunt. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=incubosem>IncubosEM</A> at: 3/1/03 5:52:50 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=naladini>naladini</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://img.ranchoweb.com/images/naladini/pills.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 913<br> <font color=#333333>(3/1/03 5:40:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8940.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: most powerfull soloer</span><hr size=1> When I was in my 40's and low 50's I was killing just about anything I wanted and the pets were extremely strong. Right about level 56 is when I really started noticing a drop off in soloing efficiency and pet strength vs. mobs (more on this perception in the last paragraph). <br>
<br>
(As a side note, many folks will point out, the epic pet can make a huge difference in soloing ability. While the epic is outclassed by the 61+ pets, it would certainly give an enormous power boost in the &lt; 60 game.)<br>
<br>
Without the epic, it is really a matter of playstyle. <br>
<br>
If you use chain pet tactics, you can generally solo higher level creatures, as long as they don't summon. <br>
<br>
If you prefer to fully buff and equip a pet and then keep it alive for several fights, you're generally better off soloing against the lowest blues.<br>
<br>
To illustrate my point, check the Hunt forums. You'll see that many of the 'popular' spots talk about mobs that go mostly lt blue within just 2-3 levels of people discovering the camp.<br>
<br>
From what I've found (when I actually have time to grind xp), is that the most effective method of soloing is exactly the method that SOE set out to nerf last fall. Killing as many 'low' dark blue mobs as you can, will generally yield more xp than killing higher level mobs more slowly. (anyone remember the &quot;Kills per hour&quot; patch message?) This still works today in the &lt;60 game, but SOE designed PoP levels and zones to prevent this from happening again.<br>
<br>
The problem with this is that as you get higher in level this becomes very tedious, as the xp curve gets a lot sharper from 56-60. Realistically, I'm soloing as efficiently as I ever have, its just that the higher levels take lots more xp to get through.<br>
<br>
